            en: 'The visitor left ar-Rabadha a changed man. He had come believing that wealth meant money, large homes, and bustling markets. He returned knowing that wealth is a contented heart — and the truly poor person is one who is never satisfied with anything.<br><br>Abu Dharr رضي الله عنه lived in ar-Rabadha until his death — content and at peace. When he sensed his end approaching, he said to his wife with a smile: <b>"Do not weep — the Messenger of Allah ﷺ told me about this moment, and I am pleased and happy!"</b>'
