            en: 'At the end of the gathering, al-Hasan al-Basri said to the man a sentence his heart kept forever: "Always look at those who have less of this world than you — not at those who have more. For whenever you look at those with less, you will see yourself as wealthy. And whenever you look at those with more, you will see yourself as poor."<br><br>The man stood up a completely different person — his heart lighter, his steps steadier. <b>He had lost his camels and his farm, but today he had discovered countless treasures that had been with him all along!</b>'
